The paper deals with coding theory and the design of error-correcting codes, which falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on repeat-accumulate codes, which are a type of concatenated code, and analyzes their performance using weight enumerators and asymptotic expressions. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of coding and communication (cs.CC), signal processing (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
